  "name": "winner_take_all",
  "description": "Proportional competition between two groups via FS lateral inhibition. Each group: 2 IB integrators + 1 FS inhibitor with self-excitation (w=15, d=2 creates ~7-spike bursts). FS cross-inhibits opposing IB (w=-30). Output ratio scales with input difference: ~2.5x for 3:1 drive, ~1.5x for 1.5:1 drive. NOT full suppression — proportional. Silent after stimulus ends. For true binary selection (only ONE winner), use command_decision_v2 or state_machine_3 instead. This is biologically realistic: cortical WTA also shows proportional competition, not winner-take-all, at moderate input differences.",
